    "long_instructions": "##### **Teacher Note**: This is Lesson 6, Level 2 from the curriculum. Notice how the shadow blocks in the workspace help to highlight the pattern for students.\r\n___\r\n\r\n#### Investigate\r\n\r\nOscar made a similar remix of Born This Way by Lady Gaga, but he did it before he knew about loops and the <code style=\"background-color: rgb(242, 24, 162); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">repeat</code> block. Now he wants to update his code to use loops instead - for example, Oscar noticed that the three <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-drum\" style=\"color: #E565F5; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Glitch Fill </span> blocks could be replaced with a repeat block!\r\n\r\nA _shadow_ of Oscar's original code is already in the workspace - your goal is to replace it with new coding blocks. As soon as you drag new blocks on top of the shadow, they'll disappear!\r\n\r\n**Do This:**\r\n1) Update Oscar's code to use a <code style=\"background-color: rgb(242, 24, 162); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">repeat</code> block. All of the blocks you need are already in the workspace - you just need to drag them to the correct places! - [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:repeat_workspace)\r\n\r\nPress the <code style=\"background-color: #fca401; color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px1 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">Run</code> button! The song should sound the same, but be easier to read and use less blocks!\r\n\r\n> If you're stuck, try clicking the <i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i> icons for hints!",
